

	Program's flags:

	-c or --compile  <filename>
	file to be compiled (mandatory)

	-o or --output  <name>
	output filename (like gcc -o)
	~ default: a.out

	-S or --source  <name>
	emmit assembly file instead of ELF
	~ default: a.s

	-T or --tape <number>
	length of brainfuck program memory (must be >= 30000)
	~ default: 30000

	-C or --cell <number (1|2|4|8)>
	cell width in terms of bytes. it can only be either 1, 2, 4 or 8
	~ default: 1

	-u or --usage:
	print usage/help

	-s or --safe
	run safe-mode emulation (check overflow/underflow, no file output)
	~ note: overwrites -E

	-E or --emu-mem
	inspect memory at @ locations (debug-mode)
	~ note: overwrites -s

	-O or --offset <number>
	memory offset to start display from (only if -E is active)
	~ default: 0

	-d or --display <number>
	how many cells to show from offset (only if -E is active)
	~ default: 100

	-g or --group <number>
	number of memory cells per row/line in display (only if -E is active)
	~ default: 10


